data.description: Welcome to the charm and elegance of this meticulously maintained two-story Victorian home nestled in the heart of Bay City's Historic District. Boasting 2,494 square feet of living space, this residence seamlessly blends timeless character with modern conveniences.  Step through the front door and be greeted by the warmth of original hardwood floors that lead you through a home adorned with countless preserved features. The wood doors, wallpaper, chandeliers, and stunning hardware on cabinets, doors, and windows are a testament to the craftsmanship of a bygone era. The main level invites you into a spacious living area anchored by an original wood-burning fireplace, complete with beautiful tilework that adds a touch of sophistication. This focal point embodies the rich history of the home. With 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms, this residence provides comfort and versatility. The kitchen is a delight with its original features such as the cabinets, adorned with stunning hardware.   A highlight of this property is the heated garage, a rare find, equipped with a 220 electrical outlet and lighting fixtures wired to respond to an Alexa. This versatile space caters to the hobbyist, DIY enthusiast, or simply those who appreciate the luxury of a heated workspace. Other updates include two central air units, two furnaces (new in 2019 and 2020), a Bose sound system throughout the home, and an outdoor sprinkler system.   This Victorian gem is not just a home; it's a piece of history waiting to be cherished by its next fortunate owner. Don't miss the opportunity to own a residence that encapsulates the elegance of a bygone era while offering the comforts of modern living.
